## 1. Open Source License: GNU AGPL v3.0

The open-source version of this project is licensed under **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)**.

### AGPL v3.0 Core Requirements (Mandatory)

1. **Open-source modifications**: If you modify the source code of this software, you must open-source your modifications under the same AGPL v3.0 license.

2. **Network use source disclosure**: If you provide services based on this software over a network (e.g., SaaS, cloud services), you must provide complete source code to users, including your modifications.

3. **Preserve copyright notices**: All copies and modified versions must retain the original copyright notices and license text.

4. **Copyleft license**: Derivative works based on this software must also be licensed under AGPL v3.0.

5. **Preserve branding and support features**: Without commercial authorization, you may not modify the software's Logo or name, nor remove or modify the "Support the Author" feature.

### Free Use Scenarios

The following scenarios are free, but must comply with all AGPL v3.0 terms:

- ✅ Personal learning, research, daily use
- ✅ Enterprise internal use (**≤1000 installations**, AGPL compliant, modifications must be open-sourced)
- ✅ Non-profit organization use
- ✅ Educational institution teaching and research
- ✅ Medical institutions and medical research organizations
- ✅ Open-source project integration (must be AGPL-compatible license)

⚠️ **Enterprise quantity note**: Enterprise internal installation/deployment exceeding 1000 copies requires a commercial license, regardless of AGPL compliance.

Full AGPL v3.0 license text: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

