## 3. FAQ

**Q: I'm an individual developer. Can I use it for free?**
A: Yes, personal use is completely free. Just comply with AGPL v3.0 (if you modify and distribute the code, you need to open-source your modifications).

**Q: Our company uses it internally. Do we need to pay?**
A: Up to 1000 installations with AGPL v3.0 compliance (modifications must be open-sourced) is free. Exceeding 1000 installations or closed-source use requires a commercial license.

**Q: I built a SaaS service based on this project. Do I need to pay?**
A: Yes. AGPL requires network services to also be open-sourced. If you don't want to disclose your source code, you need a commercial license.

**Q: Is the commercial license permanent?**
A: Commercial license terms are 3 years or more, with perpetual licensing also available. You may use the licensed version during the term. After expiration, you may renew or continue using the already-licensed version.

